other_tests.findings: Pathological examination revealed invasive ductal carcinoma, grade 3 of 3. ER, PR, and HER2 testing were negative.
Specimen contained malignant cells consistent with metastatic carcinoma.
Decreased size of the dominant mass to 3.0 cm, resolution of skin thickening, enhancement of satellite masses, and axillary lymphadenopathy.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Mass size decreased from 5.7 cm to 3.0 cm, showing clinical response to treatment.

other_tests.findings: No evidence of metastatic disease outside of the breast and axilla.
